I'd like to confirm this issue. The same behavior is exhibited (again?) when using anthropic models in AWS Bedrock. Non-Anthropic in AWS work correctly.

This is a minimized test class:
```
@RestController
public class ChatBotController {

    private final ChatClient chatClient;

    public ChatBotController(ChatClient.Builder chatClientBuilder) {
        this.chatClient = chatClientBuilder.build();
    }

    static class MyTools {

        @Tool(description = "This tool reveals the secret.")
        public String getSecret() {
            return "42 is NOT the answer";
        }
    }

    @GetMapping("/streamchat")
    public Flux<String> getMessageStream(@RequestParam String query) {

        return chatClient
                .prompt()
                .advisors(new SimpleLoggerAdvisor())
                .tools(new MyTools())
                .user(query)
                .stream()
                .content();
    }
```

As soon as I add a `@ToolParam` for my tool, it is called successfully.

I can confirm this, but would also like to add that adding:
```
    static class MyTools {

        @Tool(description = "This tool reveals the secret.")
        public String getSecret(
                @ToolParam(description = "The secret to reveal", required = false) String secret
        ) {
            return "42 is NOT the answer, it is " + secret;
        }
    }
```
also does not work. That is `ToolParam` with `required=false` prevents the tool from being invoked when streaming.
